    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer underflow in time-varying channel convolution\n\n### Summary\nThe `tv_conv` function in `multipath_tv_channel.c` suffers from integer underflow when the channel delay offset (`dd`) exceeds the number of samples (`nb_samples`). This causes incorrect memory access patterns and potential crashes.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/TOOLS/multipath_tv_channel.c`: Added bounds checking to prevent integer underflow in `tv_conv` function\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running channel simulations with high delay offsets, the system may experience:\n- Segmentation faults due to out-of-bounds memory access\n- Incorrect channel response calculations\n- Simulation hangs or crashes during channel processing\n\nThe issue manifests when `desc->channel_offset` is configured to be larger than the processing buffer length, causing the loop bound calculation `((int)nb_samples-dd)` to underflow and produce a massive iteration count.\n"
}